-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1663340399251" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/a69e8507-b94f-45e8-a9fa-3ab8d0cfc34b/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/push-ups-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="push ups using wrips wraps" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="1000px" data-height="auto" title="push ups using wrips wraps" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1702279793369" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1702279793369"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">Wrist wraps are supportive bands that are designed to stabilize and reinforce your wrist during weightlifting, powerlifting, or any other exercise that puts a lot of strain on your wrist joints. They’re usually made of durable materials, like elastic, cotton, or neoprene blends, and you wrap them around your wrist with a secure closure mechanism (usually a hook-and-loop system or twist and tuck Velcro). They offer a balance of stability and mobility and support to your wrists.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">Wrist wraps focus on supporting your wrists, limiting too much movement, reducing strain, and preventing overextension during heavy lifts or repetitive motions. They can offer compression and stability, may improve wrist alignment, and possibly help you maintain proper form.</p><p style="fon