tserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">Wrist wraps should be hand-washed with a mild soap or detergent in cold water. If you use hot water or harsh chemicals, the dye on your wraps will bleed, and you may damage the fabric and affect the elasticity. If you want a deeper clean, you can scrub them down gently and then thoroughly rinse them to remove any dirt, sweat, or odor.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">After you’re done washing them, do not even think about throwing them in the dryer! They need to be air-dried and they should be completely dry before you use them again.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1702030905188" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1702030905188" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d22f81b3-0a78-443b-9cb9-05f19feb246a/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/training-with-wrist-wraps-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athlete using wrist wraps" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="3000" height="2000" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete using wrist wraps" natural-width="3000" natural-height="2000"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1702027780359" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1702027780359"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">Always go by what the manufacturer recommends, because they know their product better than anyone. If they happen to claim, for instance, that their wraps can be washed in hot water, then you can give that a try. However, if you don’t see anything specific, stick to cold water, mild detergents, and air-drying.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;">Store your wraps in a clean and dry place away from direct sunlight or heat sources. Although you can significantly contribute to their durability by following the advice above, you shouldn’t expect to use the same wraps forever. They’re fabric, so they’re going to tear, fray, or lose their shape at some point. When that happens, all you can really do is replace them.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit !important;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660684" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660684"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660657" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660657"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I get 12- or 18-inch wrist wraps?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660793" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660793"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">If you want to fix your wrists firmly in place, choose 18-inch wrist wraps – they are more solid and give more support, especially for bigger wrists. On the other hand, if your wrists are rather thin and you don’t seek 100% stability, you may find 12-inch wraps a better option, especially for beginners.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660731" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660731"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I get stiff or flexible wrist wraps?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660709" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660709"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The choice of wrist wraps stiffness depends on your sport. If you need the highest stability, for example, for the bench press, choose stronger products. If you are into functional fitness and seek moderate support, go for flexible wrist wraps – they will give more comfort and versatility.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660688" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660688"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are wrist wraps cheating on the bench?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660743" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660743"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">No, wrist wraps aren’t cheating on the bench – they are allowed at competitions. They just provide additional support and stability for your wrists and can improve mechanics. Still, they don’t help you to press that much.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694571133" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694571133"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How long do wrist wraps last?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694542987" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694542987"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The durability of wrist wraps depends on the quality of the material and stitching. A pair of heavy-duty wrist wraps can last up for a few years of consistent use and stay in fairly good condition. Less sturdy products may show significant signs of wearing out after a few months.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694536899" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694536899"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do wrist wraps weaken your wrist?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694581118" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694581118"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Wrist wraps don’t weaken your wrists if you don’t get carried away with them. I recommend using them only for the hardest sets whether it’s about the weight or reps. Always make sure to provide some load for your forearms as well.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694575179" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694575179"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I wear wrist wraps for squats?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1665694578284" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1665694578284"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">If you feel any wrist discomfort while squatting, you can use wraps for the heaviest sets. In powerlifting, athletes often do that because of a lower barbell position on the shoulders which puts more pressure on the join